66.4	Neil_Simon	Neil Simon	Neil Simon (born July 4, 1927) is an American playwright and screenwriter. He has written numerous Broadway plays, including Brighton Beach Memoirs, Biloxi Blues, and The Odd Couple. He won the 1991 Pulitzer Prize for Drama for his play Lost In Yonkers. He has written the screenplays for several of his plays that were made into movies. He also has written the books for several musicals, including Sweet Charity.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/35/Neil_Simon_NYWTS.jpg/220px-Neil_Simon_NYWTS.jpg
